prompt:
Count the strings of length 17 over the alphabet {P, Q, R, S} that satisfy ALL five conditions simultaneously:
(a) no two adjacent letters are equal;
(b) the letter R appears exactly five times;
(c) the letter P is never immediately followed by the letter Q (the substring "PQ" never occurs);
(d) the first letter and the last letter of the string are different;
(e) the letter Q appears an even number of times (zero counts as even).
Give the exact count. Put the final integer inside \boxed{}.
